  cells, dendritic calcium transients evoked by climbing fiber inputs were
  clearly observed in anesthetised mice with a high SNR and fast decay time.
  These characteristics of Cal-520 are a great advantage over those of Oregon
  Green BAPTA-1, the most commonly used calcium indicator dye, for monitoring
  the activity of individual neurons both in vitro and in vivo.%
